WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.234 --> 00:00:02.402
-Thank you so much
for doing the show.

00:00:02.402 --> 00:00:05.938
Last time I saw you,
you didn't have an Oscar.

00:00:05.938 --> 00:00:08.074
You have an Academy Award?
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:00:08.074 --> 00:00:10.610
No!
-It's crazy, man.

00:00:10.610 --> 00:00:12.078
It's crazy.
-What's that feel --

00:00:12.078 --> 00:00:14.747
I mean,
we were talking about the film,

00:00:14.747 --> 00:00:16.315
and then,
for it to get nominated

00:00:16.315 --> 00:00:18.818
was just a goal in itself.
-Yeah, yeah.

00:00:18.818 --> 00:00:20.653
-But then you won.
-What the hell, right?

00:00:20.653 --> 00:00:22.188
[ Laughter ]

00:00:22.188 --> 00:00:23.889
You know,
it's just one of those things,

00:00:23.889 --> 00:00:26.359
man, where you play basketball
your entire life...

00:00:26.359 --> 00:00:27.460
-Yeah.

00:00:27.460 --> 00:00:28.928
-...and then you move on
to something else.

00:00:28.928 --> 00:00:31.131
And you wind up
working with great people.

00:00:31.131 --> 00:00:33.099
-Yeah.
-And the next thing you know,

00:00:33.099 --> 00:00:34.534
you're sitting at the Osc--
I mean, I was sitting there

00:00:34.534 --> 00:00:35.634
with Vanessa at the Oscars like,

00:00:35.634 --> 00:00:37.236
"What in the hell
are we doing here?"

00:00:37.236 --> 00:00:38.905
[ Laughter ]
-"How did I get here?"

00:00:38.905 --> 00:00:41.207
-Yeah, "What --
Meryl Streep's right there."

00:00:41.207 --> 00:00:42.741
[ Laughter ]

00:00:42.741 --> 00:00:45.077
-Speaking of surrounding
yourself with good people,

00:00:45.077 --> 00:00:48.247
who are these young ladies
right here on the cover?

00:00:48.247 --> 00:00:51.818
-The one with the eyebrow there
and all the attitude,

00:00:51.818 --> 00:00:53.385
that's our middle daughter,
Gianna.

00:00:53.385 --> 00:00:55.254
-Oh, yeah.

00:00:55.254 --> 00:00:56.922
-And this is
our basketball team.

00:00:56.922 --> 00:00:58.958
These are the girls
that I coach every single day.

00:00:58.958 --> 00:01:00.627
-Now, you coach them
every single day.

00:01:00.627 --> 00:01:03.296
-Every day.
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:01:03.296 --> 00:01:07.100
-How's it to have Kobe Bryant
be a coach?

00:01:07.100 --> 00:01:08.301
How are you as a coach?

00:01:08.301 --> 00:01:09.702
I mean, you've worked
with some of the best.

00:01:09.702 --> 00:01:11.737
But I mean, what do you --
-[ Laughs ]

00:01:11.737 --> 00:01:13.573
I mean, listen,
we practice every day.

00:01:13.573 --> 00:01:14.674
-You do?
-Yes.

00:01:14.674 --> 00:01:16.843
So, like,
Gianna wants to play at UConn.

00:01:16.843 --> 00:01:18.711
I have a few kids
that want to go to Stanford.

00:01:18.711 --> 00:01:20.212
Some want to go
to Notre Dame and play.

00:01:20.212 --> 00:01:22.415
And it's like,
"Listen, three days a week

00:01:22.415 --> 00:01:23.649
ain't gonna get you there,
right?

00:01:23.649 --> 00:01:24.750
You got to really work."

00:01:24.750 --> 00:01:26.285
And so
we run the triangle offense.

00:01:26.285 --> 00:01:27.453
-No.

00:01:27.453 --> 00:01:28.922
-Oh, yeah, the girls
run the triangle offense.

00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:30.757
-I mean, that is insane.
-Yeah.

00:01:30.757 --> 00:01:32.926
-Does Phil Jackson know this?
[ Laughter ]

00:01:32.926 --> 00:01:35.562
-So, he does, actually.
So, I'll --

00:01:35.562 --> 00:01:36.929
The girls really ran, like,

00:01:36.929 --> 00:01:39.765
a really complicated
triangle-offensive sequence.

00:01:39.765 --> 00:01:41.267
-Yeah, it is tricky.
-It is tricky.

00:01:41.267 --> 00:01:42.869
And I sent him
the video of them running it.

00:01:42.869 --> 00:01:44.404
-Did you really?
-I did, and he was like,

00:01:44.404 --> 00:01:46.472
"Oh, my gosh.
They ran it beautifully."

00:01:46.472 --> 00:01:47.606
And I was like, "Yeah, well,

00:01:47.606 --> 00:01:49.175
they kind of got
a better coach, so..."

00:01:49.175 --> 00:01:51.211
[ Laughter ]

00:01:51.211 --> 00:01:53.012
It's okay, man.
It's all right, man.

00:01:53.012 --> 00:01:55.114
-That's so cool
that you did that.

00:01:55.114 --> 00:01:57.116
I got to say congrats
to you and Vanessa.

00:01:57.116 --> 00:01:59.718
You're expecting another girl.
Another Bryant.

00:01:59.718 --> 00:02:01.754
[ Cheers and applause ]
-Yes!

00:02:01.754 --> 00:02:04.089
Four girls, man.
Four girls.

00:02:04.089 --> 00:02:06.559
-Four girls?
-Four girls.

00:02:06.559 --> 00:02:08.360
-All women in the house, dude.

00:02:08.360 --> 00:02:09.796
-I spend most of the time
at the house

00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:11.664
literally talking to myself.

00:02:11.664 --> 00:02:13.066
[ Laughter ]

00:02:13.066 --> 00:02:15.268
I think they're listening --
-Oh, yeah, they are.

00:02:15.268 --> 00:02:16.802
-And then, they just go off
talking about something else,

00:02:16.802 --> 00:02:19.538
and I just face the wall.
[ Laughter ]

00:02:19.538 --> 00:02:21.140
-Wow.
That is gonna be wild, man.

00:02:21.140 --> 00:02:22.408
-It's nuts.
It's awesome, though.

00:02:22.408 --> 00:02:24.077
-Are they excited
to get a sister?

00:02:24.077 --> 00:02:25.845
-Yeah, they are.
Really, really excited.

00:02:25.845 --> 00:02:27.913
Our eldest --
her and Gianna both

00:02:27.913 --> 00:02:29.582
do a great job looking out
for Bianka right.

00:02:29.582 --> 00:02:31.951
-It's the best news,
having a baby.

00:02:31.951 --> 00:02:33.953
-It's awesome, man.
-It's the greatest.

00:02:33.953 --> 00:02:36.756
I heard somewhere that you said
that your youngest daughters,

00:02:36.756 --> 00:02:38.191
you're not even gonna, like --

00:02:38.191 --> 00:02:40.192
that you don't want them
to really know you as

00:02:40.192 --> 00:02:43.062
an NBA legend
or your basketball past.

00:02:43.062 --> 00:02:45.665
-Yeah.
-You think they're gonna

00:02:45.665 --> 00:02:47.467
know you as something different?

00:02:47.467 --> 00:02:50.235
-Well, yeah, they'll never
actually see me play.

00:02:50.235 --> 00:02:51.437
You know what I mean?

00:02:51.437 --> 00:02:53.172
So they'll be like,
"Wait. You played ball?

00:02:53.172 --> 00:02:54.240
What?"
[ Laughter ]

00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:56.676
-"Whatever, Dad."
-"What? Whatever.

00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:59.077
I can outshoot you,"
and that sort of stuff.

00:02:59.077 --> 00:03:00.746
Yeah, because Bianka's 2,

00:03:00.746 --> 00:03:03.015
so she doesn't know me
as a basketball player.

00:03:03.015 --> 00:03:04.284
-You think they know as, like,

00:03:04.284 --> 00:03:05.751
a writer and director
and producer.

00:03:05.751 --> 00:03:07.553
-How about that?
-I think that's pretty cool.

00:03:07.553 --> 00:03:09.322
I like that, actually.
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:03:09.322 --> 00:03:13.425
-It's awesome.
-That's amazing.

00:03:13.425 --> 00:03:15.662
I'm pretty sure they'll know you
as a basketball player, too.

00:03:15.662 --> 00:03:16.862
[ Laughter ]

00:03:16.862 --> 00:03:18.965
I want to talk about this.
This is awesome.

00:03:18.965 --> 00:03:21.901
This is the "Wizenard" series.

00:03:21.901 --> 00:03:24.637
Now, this is a mix of fantasy,

00:03:24.637 --> 00:03:27.440
almost like, I'd say,
"Harry Potter"

00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:29.642
or "Game of Thrones,"
mixed with basketball.

00:03:29.642 --> 00:03:31.544
-Yeah.
I had to try and describe it

00:03:31.544 --> 00:03:32.978
to somebody when I first
came up with the idea.

00:03:32.978 --> 00:03:34.380
They're like, "What is it?

00:03:34.380 --> 00:03:36.482
You got to give, like, elevator
pitch, elevator pitch."

00:03:36.482 --> 00:03:37.583
-Elevator, yeah.

00:03:37.583 --> 00:03:39.518
What can you pitch me
in an elevator?

00:03:39.518 --> 00:03:42.788
-"Harry Potter," Olympics,
had a baby.

00:03:42.788 --> 00:03:43.823
This is what we're making.

00:03:43.823 --> 00:03:45.258
[ Laughter ]

00:03:45.258 --> 00:03:47.293
And they look at me kind of
weird, but, "Okay, I get it."

00:03:47.293 --> 00:03:49.295
-And that is what you made.
-Yeah.

00:03:49.295 --> 00:03:50.696
-And who is Wesley King?

00:03:50.696 --> 00:03:53.999
-Wesley King's the author.
You know, just brilliant.

00:03:53.999 --> 00:03:56.836
This is five books in one.

00:03:56.836 --> 00:03:58.137
So it's told
from the perspective

00:03:58.137 --> 00:03:59.772
of five different athletes.

00:03:59.772 --> 00:04:03.376
And he managed to write
five books simultaneously,

00:04:03.376 --> 00:04:04.744
and he's just
absolutely brilliant.

00:04:04.744 --> 00:04:08.181
I don't know how he did it.
[ Laughs ]

00:04:08.181 --> 00:04:09.314
-It's amazing.
-But he did it, yeah.

00:04:09.314 --> 00:04:11.784
-But there's great stuff
in here,

00:04:11.784 --> 00:04:14.020
if you like that fantasy world
and the wizards.

00:04:14.020 --> 00:04:17.957
But also, really good advice
and coaching stuff,

00:04:17.957 --> 00:04:20.293
things you do learn
if you're on a good team.

00:04:20.293 --> 00:04:23.029
-Well, yeah, the important thing
in this story

00:04:23.029 --> 00:04:25.130
is the story of self-acceptance.

00:04:25.130 --> 00:04:27.200
We all have fears,
and we all have anxieties

00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:29.735
and things of that nature.
We can't ignore them.

00:04:29.735 --> 00:04:31.170
When you ignore them,
they fester,

00:04:31.170 --> 00:04:32.438
and they have control over you.

00:04:32.438 --> 00:04:35.007
What these young men
have to learn through magic

00:04:35.007 --> 00:04:37.243
is how to have the courage
to face those fears

00:04:37.243 --> 00:04:38.945
and use those fears
to help themselves

00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:41.414
be better basketball players
and better people through it.

00:04:41.414 --> 00:04:42.982
So that's the journey.
-That's right.

00:04:42.982 --> 00:04:47.386
Good for you.
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:04:47.386 --> 00:04:49.889
"The Wizenard" series.

00:04:49.889 --> 00:04:51.757
Actually, I heard
that you were thinking maybe

00:04:51.757 --> 00:04:53.426
making this into
a Broadway production?

00:04:53.426 --> 00:04:54.827
-Yes.
-Really?

00:04:54.827 --> 00:04:55.995
-Yes.
[ Cheers ]

00:04:55.995 --> 00:04:57.196
-And that you might be
getting someone fun

00:04:57.196 --> 00:04:58.764
to help out
write some of the songs?

00:04:58.764 --> 00:05:00.833
-Somebody standing --
sitting right over there.

00:05:00.833 --> 00:05:04.303
-Tariq.
[ Cheers and applause ]

00:05:04.303 --> 00:05:06.839
-I mean, listen.

00:05:06.839 --> 00:05:10.043
I mean, as a lyricist,
he's extremely well-known.

00:05:10.043 --> 00:05:11.244
-Yeah.
He's the best.

00:05:11.244 --> 00:05:12.778
-He does okay. Right?
-He does okay, yeah.

00:05:12.778 --> 00:05:14.747
-So, I'm like, you know,
if I'm gonna go to somebody

00:05:14.747 --> 00:05:16.448
to write this thing...
-You go to the best.

00:05:16.448 --> 00:05:18.317
-Come on.
-Oh, I see what you're gonna do.

00:05:18.317 --> 00:05:21.321
You just got the Oscar.
Now you're gonna get the Tony,

00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:22.989
and then you're
gonna get a Grammy.

00:05:22.989 --> 00:05:25.591
You're going to be the first
athlete to ever have an EGOT.

00:05:25.591 --> 00:05:27.260
-Yeah.
-That's gonna happen.

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:28.961
Mark my words.
There you go right there.

00:05:28.961 --> 00:05:31.230
[ Cheers and applause ]
I'm so happy for you.

00:05:31.230 --> 00:05:32.631
Congrats on the baby.
-Thank you.

00:05:32.631 --> 00:05:34.833
-Congrats on the Oscar.
Congrats on the book.

00:05:34.833 --> 00:05:36.268
Kobe Bryant's new book

00:05:36.268 --> 00:05:40.573
"The Wizenard Series:
Training Camp" is out today.

